04/01/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- War crimes prosecutor Vladimir Vukcevic said on Sunday (January 3rd) that authorities are searching for two remaining war crimes fugitives -- Ratko Mladic and Goran Hadzic -- 24 hours a day. Vuckevic predicted that the two will be located and brought to justice this year. He also stressed that co-operation between his office and prosecution offices in the region is solid. (RTS, Tanjug - 03/01/10)
